Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Oval handle to sharp turn. Rectangular stamp with caduceus and cornucopia symbols. Clay fine light brown; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) has several drawings of this type. Name Imas.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0928)
